cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CE, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the development of a cloud infrastructure for processing and analyzing large and complex metabolomics datasets. This involves the use of multiple types of algorithms and workflows, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the computational scaling behavior of the platform, which suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB) and performance evaluation (cs.CE). Finally, the economic analysis of running on cloud platforms suggests a focus on optimization and resource allocation (cs.NE).
